    <h2>Sentence Correction</h2>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="question">
            <p><strong>Question 1:</strong> Identify the incorrect part in the sentence:<br>
            "Each of the students in the class have submitted their assignments."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="solution">
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> The error is in "have submitted." "Each" is singular, so it should be "has submitted."</p>
            <p>Correct sentence: "Each of the students in the class has submitted their assignments."</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Reading Comprehension</h2>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="question">
            <p><strong>Question 2:</strong> Read the passage and answer the question:<br>
            "Despite technological advancements, many ancient techniques of agriculture still hold relevance today. The ability to combine traditional methods with modern innovations has led to a sustainable approach to farming."<br>
            What is the primary idea of this passage?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="solution">
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> The main idea of the passage is the importance of integrating ancient agricultural methods with modern technology to ensure sustainability.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Para Jumbles</h2>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="question">
            <p><strong>Question 3:</strong> Arrange the sentences in a logical sequence:<br>
            (A) This has made the availability of information faster and more efficient.<br>
            (B) The digital age has revolutionized communication.<br>
            (C) However, it has also led to challenges such as information overload.<br>
            (D) With a single click, we can access vast amounts of data.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="solution">
            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> The correct sequence is: B - A - D - C.</p>
            <p>Explanation: The paragraph starts with the digital revolution (B), followed by its impact (A), an example (D), and ends with a challenge (C).</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
